History: Status post bronch, question interval improvement. CHEST, SINGLE AP PORTABLE VIEW. Compared with earlier the same day 12:17, there is somewhat improved aeration in the left lung. A dense opacity previously seen in the left mid and upper zones now shows partial aeration with residual patchy opacity. The left hemidiaphragm is likely still elevated. No definite pneumothorax is identified. Subcutaneous emphysema again noted. Left chest tube is present, unchanged. Aside from some atelectasis at the right base and possible minimal blunting of the right costophrenic angle, the right lung remains grossly clear. Mediastinum remains midline. The tracheal contour is grossly unchanged.
Impression: Partial reexpansion of the left lung. Probable elevated left hemidiaphragm.
